  "why": "The paper enforces naturalness and semantic validity of inputs by only mutating MDP initial states conservatively, validating each mutated initial state with the environment, and using small, bounded random perturbations. However, mutations are performed relative to the currently selected seed (which may itself be a prior mutant) and the paper does not describe mechanisms that bound cumulative distortion relative to the original seed across multiple mutation iterations. Thus MDPFuzz controls realism and semantic consistency at each mutation step but does not prevent gradual drift over repeated iterations.",
